text_a: The football team had worked hard all season. They had won every game and made it to the championship. There were only seconds left on the clock and the game was tied. The quarterback through a long pass and the receiver scored.
text_b: The crowd booed the team loudly.

text_a: Newly married, Sue liked to cook for her husband. Unfortunately Sue was a terrible cook. Bob ate her food anyway and told her it was good. On their first anniversary Bob gave Sue cooking lessons.
text_b: She became a better cook.

text_a: Lewis knew the cave like the back of his hand. Five first-time cavers walked behind him. Suddenly, a few bats flew down from the darkness above. All the people but Lewis ran back towards the cave's entrance.
text_b: Lewis laughed and told them not be afraid of the bats.

text_a: Amy was very stressed out all the time. A friend suggested that she try meditation. Amy was skeptical, but she agreed to give it a shot. She went to a class and breathed and focused.
text_b: It helped her mental state immensely.

text_a: Bethany was self-conscious about her arm hair. She tried shaving it off. It grew back within a few weeks. She got a laser hair removal treatment.
text_b: She felt better about herself.

text_a: School was just a disaster today. It was raining and everyone got soaked in the rain. There was also a fire and everyone had to evacuate the school. I caught a fever from being in the rain for several minutes.
text_b: I went swimming in the lake.

text_a: Ally wished for her boyfriend to pick her out a beautiful ring. She left jewelry store fliers on the counter. Next, she circled rings in magazines. She even mentioned them out loud in phone conversations.
text_b: Ally was very subtle.

text_a: There is a cemetery with 199 grave stones. 12 men brought a casket. 12 men put the casket in the ground. Men and women wept together.
text_b: They mourned for losses.

text_a: My girlfriend collects stamps. Not the kind for mail but the kind to stamp things with. She has different cute ones. For her birthday I want to buy her more.
text_b: I bought her sexy lingerie instead.

text_a: Addie was working at the mall at Hollister when a strange man came in. Before she knew it, Addie looked behind her and saw stolen clothes. Addie got scared and tried to chase the man out. Luckily guards came and arrested him.
text_b: Addie was put in jail for her crime.

text_a: My wife had MLK day off. She slept in, and did not get up until 10 AM. We had a leisurely breakfast. She watched Little House on the Prairie while I surfed the net.
text_b: The day was very stressful.

text_a: Amy arrived home from volleyball practice and sat on the couch. Her mother walked in and gasped. She told Amy she needed to shower since she was sweaty. They argued since Amy thought it was no big deal.
text_b: Amy left for volleyball practice.

text_a: He watched in anger from outside the window. The lovers were oblivious to his presence. He burst through the door and was atop them in moments. The other man struggled but he was too weak to prevent his own demise.
text_b: His cheating wife called the police and he was arrested.

text_a: Amy was unsatisfied with her paper. Instead of turning it in, she skipped class. She went to a coffee shop to rewrite. She produced a paper she was proud of.
text_b: Amy got an A on the paper but in trouble for skipping class.

text_a: Zack and his friends passed a scary house on their walks to school. One day, they decided to go inside it. Zack and his friends went inside every room. The house was old and abandoned.
text_b: They decided to play baseball there.

text_a: Chris was on his second layover of the week. Pacing around the airport, he decided he would make use of this time. Installing an app on his phone, he began practicing his french. Another patron of the airport overheard him and offered him assistance
text_b: The patron didn't understand Chris because he only spoke Chinese.

text_a: Gina's phone died as they drove on the highway. She plugged it in the front seat, but she was in the backseat. She was bored without her phone so she tried to reach it. She was on the end and it was too far.
text_b: Gina doesn't care about electronics.

text_a: Jon and Mika wanted a baby daughter. After years of trying, they finally conceived a baby girl. Unfortunately, the baby had complications. Jon and Mika were scared that the baby would die.
text_b: Jon and Mika then gave birth to a boy.

text_a: Charles had a big, white dog. He did not like the way the dog looked. Charles thought about what he could do to change it. He painted the dog pink.
text_b: Charles mother was very angry.

text_a: Rocket was the nickname of Jose. He was nicknamed that because of his speed. One day he was running track at school tournament. He won first place as the fastest kid in school.
text_b: Jose was embarrassed that he had lost.

text_a: My friend went out one night looking to find love. He ended up getting pretty drunk. The next thing we knew he was flirting with a gay man. After a while, we lost track of our friend.
text_b: Our friend ended up home at three am with a girl.

text_a: One summer my sister and I set up a lemonade stand. It was the first month at a new house and we didn't know anyone. Few people walked by and even fewer stopped. The old pastor walked over from next door.
text_b: He poured our lemonade onto the ground.

text_a: Marcy wondered about the kids. She had been in the kitchen and hadn't heard them in awhile. Usually, when the kids were quiet, they were getting into something. Marcy looked in the bedrooms and didn't see them.
text_b: She found them in the living room reading and was relieved.

text_a: John was a student in law school. He was having a tough time learning all of the material. John decided to do something about this. He met with the professors and got extra tutoring.
text_b: Pretty soon, he was up to speed and feeling much more confident.

text_a: Sarah had a fear of being around others. She decided to force herself to go to a party. At the party, she became dizzy and nervous. Sarah decided this was enough, and went to see a therapist.
text_b: The therapist taught her ways to cope with her problem.

text_a: Ted's parents told him to focus on studies and not on games. Ted thought that games were a burgeoning art form, worthy of praise. Ted started to write reviews and articles about different games. The reviews and articles were published in national magazines.
text_b: His parents relented.

text_a: Kayla borrowed a book from her sister. She brought the book with her to a coffee shop to read. Kayla accidentally spilled some of her vanilla latte on the book. She immediately went home to inform her sister.
text_b: Kayla was an only child.

text_a: Amy's sister took her to the beach to surf on her vacation. Amy hurriedly suited up in her wetsuit. The instructor was patient when Amy couldn't get the hang of it. Finally it was time for Amy to try on her own.
text_b: Amy was surprised that she did a good job.

text_a: A scientist discovers that there is a disease beginning to spread. He works on a cure for the disease in his lab. Other scientists gather to help him with his work. Several weeks go by and they manage to develop a cure.
text_b: They save the world.

text_a: Linda began to have problems with a coworker at her job. The coworker had started bossing her around at work. The coworker even talked behind her back. Linda went to her boss with the issue and the boss mediated them.
text_b: Her boss fired her the next day.

text_a: Daddy took us to the woods to camp. He taught us how to build a fire with sticks. He helped us learn how to make our own tents. We fell asleep counting the stars in the sky.
text_b: We had a wonderful time camping.

text_a: I got a job as a shopping mall Santa last December. The hours were long. The pay was bad. But I found interacting with the kids to be completely amazing.
text_b: I found that playing Santa was not worth my time off.

text_a: Ben lost his job. He was devastated since he loved his job. Months went by and he could not find a job in his field. So, he started to worry that he would never find a job.
text_b: But then he did find a job.

text_a: Last night I attended a cocktail party. I wore my new white dress. Everyone at the party loved it. However to my dismay I spilled wine all over it.
text_b: I was wearing a red dress.

text_a: I was walking to the store recently. As I was passing an exit, I felt cold, hard steel on my arm. I was shocked that I was being hit by a car! The driver was very apologetic after he saw I was hit.
text_b: The driver of the car became very angry at me.

text_a: Sal was mad that his parents were moving. They were moving to the eighth floor of a building. He hated living that high. After moving, he took a look out his bedroom window.
text_b: Sal tossed his pillow out the window.

text_a: Maggie noticed a bat was flying around her ceiling. She panicked and didn't know what to do. She decided to hide in her room and call the exterminator. Suddenly, her cat comes in her room holding something in his mouth.
text_b: It was the bat.

text_a: Amayah's birthday is coming up. She will be five Year's old. Her mom is throwing her a princess party. She is invited a lot of her friends from school.
text_b: Amayah is happy to be the princess at her party.

text_a: Morgan loved tea. She bought a travel mug to bring tea with her to school. She drank all of her tea on the drive to school. So, when she got to school, she had to fill up with more hot water.
text_b: Morgan was glad she remembered to bring extra tea bags with her.

text_a: Joey was camping with his friends. He wanted to start a fire to roast marshmallows. He found some sticks and logs in the woods. He used a match to light the logs.
text_b: Then he roasted marshmallows.

text_a: Johnny wanted a change from his big city life in Boston. He decided he would be happier in America's Heartland. Finally the day had arrived, Johnny moved to Idaho. He had escaped the big city life.
text_b: Johnny began planning to move to Boston.

text_a: Betsy wanted a puppy, but her mom said no. Betsy was so sad and disappointed because she really wanted a pet. One day she went into her room and found a hamster in a cage. Her mom had gotten her a pet after all!
text_b: Betsy threw a fit because it was basically a rodent.

text_a: Bob was at the grocery store. At check out, he realized he forgot his credit card. The woman behind him offered to buy his groceries. Bob was so appreciative.
text_b: Bob ran away in terror.

text_a: Ty was nervous about attending summer camp not knowing anyone. The first day, he met Sam playing soccer. That night, he met Brenda at the campfire. At breakfast the next morning, he met Bill.
text_b: They all hung out without him and he felt excluded.

text_a: I got a new truck. To celebrate, i went mudding. I drove through lots of mud puddles. my truck got really dirty.
text_b: Afterwards, I washed my truck in the driveway.

text_a: Valerie decided she wanted to learn German. She signed up for a class to teach her. When she wasn't in class, she studied very hard. Soon, she decided to practice speaking German with a German friend.
text_b: Valerie wanted to visit Germany.

text_a: I hate doing laundry. Matching socks is a horrible waste of time. Everytime i do laundry socks get lost. i was tired of searching for matching socks.
text_b: I threw out all my old socks and bought all plain white socks.

text_a: Rick was trying to go to sleep. But there was a fly flying around his room. The noise of it was so irritating. But he was too exhausted to try to catch the fly.
text_b: While he was sleeping, the bee stung him.

text_a: Rob has never been on a rollercoaster. Rob's friends offered him a free ticket to six flags. Rob decided he may as well join. They all went and waited a long line.
text_b: Rob had generous friends.

text_a: Cindy was at a restaurant. And she ordered hot soup. But the waitress forgot to tell her that the bowl was hot. So when received the bowl from the waitress, she hurt her hands.
text_b: Cindy continued holding the soup.

text_a: Neil was backpacking Europe. He had just arrived in Dover. He loved how friendly the people were! He also loved their delicious food.
text_b: Neil was having a great time.

text_a: Gina was in trouble for something her sister did. Her parents held her accountable since she was older. Gina thought this was very unfair. She went to her room and sat alone, waiting for an apology.
text_b: Her sister came and apologized.

text_a: When I was sixteen I learned to drive. The first time I got into the car I lost track of the brake pedal. I didn't know how to stop! My dad had to turn on the emergency brake.
text_b: My dad then took me to get my license.

text_a: Jon's fridge was broken. He called a service company to repair it. They told him they could come the next day at noon. Jon met them at the door when they arrived, and let them in.
text_b: The company fixed his television.

text_a: Lars realizes that a lot of snow had accumulated on his deck. He decides he should shovel some of the snow. Lars works long all afternoon until the snow is cleared. When he is done, he goes inside for a shower.
text_b: When he gets out of the shower he shovels his deck.

text_a: Gina's family pulled into a rest stop off the highway. Gina got out and stretched her legs. At the stop there was a gas station and a Burger King. Gina normally didn't like Burger King's fries.
text_b: Gina walked down the highway without her family.

text_a: We went hiking a few weeks ago. After deciding to leave, we decided on a forest not too far from us. Once we got there, the weather was perfect! After setting out down the trail, we saw a snake!
text_b: We were scared!

text_a: Harvey's roommates teased him about being so thin. They were egotistical football players. They challenged Harvey to a ping pong game, expecting him to lose. But they did not know that Harvey was a nationally ranked player.
text_b: Harvey choked, and lost every match he played.

text_a: Alyssa got some coffee on the way to work. She drank the coffee as she drove. Suddenly, she had to quickly stop her car. The coffee spilt all over her lap, scalding her legs.
text_b: She almost had an accident as she screamed out in pain.

text_a: Jane wanted long hair. So she let it grow for months and months. But it became difficult to take care of. And when it was summer, hair long hair made her too hot.
text_b: Jane decided to cut her hair short for summer.

text_a: Drake attended a party on Friday. He discovered that his wallet had been stolen from his coat. Drake immediately called the police, but the wallet was not found. Drake confronted the host of the party about the issue.
text_b: Drake told the host he wanted to attend his parties again.

text_a: I turned on the news one day. I saw sad news that there were hostages in a venue. I watched for a while and they said the hostages were shot. I cried and held my girlfriend who was with me.
text_b: I think violence is inspiring.

text_a: Last week the internet went out. My wife and I were bored out of our minds. Every other option available seemed boring. Eventually we just drank and talked for a while.
text_b: We ended up having a fun time after all.

text_a: Jared was grounded for a week. He never cleaned his room. His parents told him he would get days off for dusting. He went around dusting the entire house.
text_b: His parents gave him three days off.

text_a: Rick was at the bar when he saw a driver license on the ground. He asked around if it was anybody's there. Of course it wasn't, and Rick didn't want to leave it with a stranger. So he decided to drive to the address of the license owner.
text_b: Rick gave the license to the driver and made the driver happy.

text_a: I decided to pay a visit to someone I've been dating online. I never seen her in person, but I trust her. The airplane flight took several hours. When I arrived at the hotel, she said she's in front.
text_b: I got on the plane and flew home.

text_a: Andrew was getting married tomorrow. He had bought the wedding ring months before and couldn't find it! He looked everywhere in his house. Finally he remembered that it was back at the store to get resized.
text_b: Andrew was so relieved.

text_a: Juan wanted to be a luchador. He grew up watching them on television. He practiced every day in the basement. Eventually he got added to small shows.
text_b: Juan decided that being  luchador was a stupid aspiration.

text_a: A young girl named Taylor had always wanted a pet. One day her mother surprised her with a trip to the pet store. They both entered the store and looked around. Taylor had a hard time deciding which animal to adopt.
text_b: Taylor decided instead to go clothes shopping.

text_a: Jennifer was hungry on a rainy day. She looked through her house, but didn't have much. Suddenly, she noticed a can on her shelf. She looked at it and it was chicken noodle soup.
text_b: Jennifer opened the can and began to eat.

text_a: One Friday night we all pitched in and got a huge pizza. My brother bit into a slice that had a piece of gum on it. Disgusted, we called the pizza place to complain. They came by our house and denied everything.
text_b: They apologized and gave us another pizza.

text_a: Mark had a big interview for a new job. He prepared himself for the questions they may ask. The interviewer seemed to be impressed with Mark's answers. The interviewer informed Mark he had the job.
text_b: Mark was enraged and stormed out.

text_a: Tom was wrapping Christmas presents. But he lost track of who they were for. So he put wrong name tags on the presents. On Christmas, Tom handed his son a present.
text_b: His son was bewildered when he unwrapped a dollhouse.

text_a: Beth started collecting dolls. She bought dolls online and at flea markets and antique shops. Soon Beth's house was full of dolls. When a friend came to visit, there was no room to chat in the house.
text_b: They had to move the dolls to sit down.

text_a: Eddie liked to watch people use metal detectors on the beach. He watched one man for a while. It had been over an hour and the man hadn't found anything yet. Eddie secretly buried a pile of quarters in the sand.
text_b: The man sadly found nothing that day.

text_a: Every summer Brad and Ashley go swimming in the river. Sometimes they float on inner tubes for hours enjoying the cool water. They can not go to the river this year. Ashley broke her leg and can not be in the water.
text_b: Ashley told Brad to go without her.

text_a: Gina's local library had no books on dolphins. She needed to find another library. The closest one was downtown. Her mother refused to take her.
text_b: Gina decided to walk instead.

text_a: Morris buys himself a skateboard to stay active. He brings the skateboard to the park for a day of skateboarding. He notices that he is much older than the other people there. However, they welcome him, and they don't seem to mind his age.
text_b: Morris was bullied everyday at the skate park.

text_a: One day Matilda was extremely bored. So she picked a name and address out of the phone book. She wrote a silly letter to that random person. And the recipient wrote back to Matilda!
text_b: Matilda then got a letter from her brother.

text_a: Joe was helping his dad clear the woods in the back of their yard. All of a sudden he heard loud buzzing. He had stirred up a bee's nest. He got stung six times before he could escape.
text_b: Joe laughed about the experience.

text_a: It was summer and Gina and her sister were bored. They decided to watch music videos. There was the music video channel or the black entertainment channel. They chose to watch the black entertainment channel.
text_b: Gina and her sister had a great time together.

text_a: Mary liked to drink coffee every morning. Today she was in a hurry. She went to a drive through coffee place. She noticed the coffee was the wrong order after she drove away.
text_b: Mary crashed into a poll.

text_a: Amy was excited it was Christmas Eve. She had been very good all year. She gave the list of her favorite toys to Santa at the mall. He told her she would receive everything she wanted.
text_b: On Christmas, Amy got exactly what she hoped to get.

text_a: Our parents took us to Paragon Park in 1963. We took a ferry from Rowes Wharf in Boston. We rode the carousel, the whip, and the caterpillar. We played skeeball.
text_b: We have many fond memories of this childhood trip.

text_a: Bob was really thirsty and wanted a soda. Unfortunately, he didn't have any money. Bob walked into a gas station and asked if he could have a soda. The cashier asked him if he had any money.
text_b: He decided to go for a run.

text_a: Bella sat by the campfire with her friends. They all had s'mores dangling over the fire, warming up. Each one of them took turns telling a scary story. When it was her turn she made sure to put her best acting to use.
text_b: Bella's friends were very frightened by her story.

text_a: Rick told his friends that he hated camping. They bugged him until he went camping anyway. One night, he awoke to a snake in his tent. He ran screaming from the tent.
text_b: Rick refuses to even think about going camping now.

text_a: Ava needed to go shopping with her two-year old. But she couldn't find his shoes even after looking everywhere! She decided she had no choice but to buy him new shoes. She carried him into the store in order to select a new pair.
text_b: Ava was a neglectful mother.

text_a: I always try to go to bed on time. Last night I was hooked watching a new tv show. Before I knew it it was really late. I should have been asleep hours ago.
text_b: I hated the television show.

text_a: Robbie and I went to a fancy restaurant for our anniversary. It was very elegant. We both had to dress formally in order to get a table. We enjoyed TEN courses over four hours.
text_b: Robbie and I wore shorts to the restaurant.

text_a: Tina is very tired every single morning. She does not get enough sleep because of her two jobs. Tina decides to quit one of the jobs. She now gets enough sleep to function everyday.
text_b: Tina is well rested.

text_a: Betsy was about to celebrate her sixteenth birthday. Her parents surprised her with a nice dinner out and a small present. Happily, her parents gave her a monogram necklace. On the way home, Betsy misplaced the necklace in the car.
text_b: Betsy wore the monogrammed necklace when she turned 14.

text_a: David asked his mother if he could pour his own drink. His mother agreed, but warned him to be careful. David accidentally knocked over his glass which shattered everywhere. His mother cheerfully forgave David.
text_b: David ate a cheeseburger.

text_a: Jon felt like a bad dad. He worked so late, he often missed his kids when he came home. On the weekends, he was tired and grumpy. One Saturday, his son sat down on the couch and leaned on Jon's arm.
text_b: Jon loved spending time with the kids.

text_a: Ed and his twin Ethan were looking at women online. Then they saw a profile for two twin ladies. They called Sami and Sara and arranged a date. On their date, all four had a wonderful time.
text_b: Years later both couples got married.

text_a: Joe and Mary invited friends over for dinner. The gathered in the kitchen and prepared pizza. As the pizza cooked, the couples got board games. The played games for hours.
text_b: The all decided to never do it again.

text_a: Zoey was taunted by her friends for having a strange name. She liked her name and wished people wouldn't be so mean. A new show was made that had a main character named Zoey. Zoey's name suddenly became very cool to her peers.
text_b: Zoey was happy that everyone liked her name now.

text_a: Paul wanted to buy his wife a gift. Unfortunately he couldn't decide what to get. He fretted over it for days. Eventually it was his wife's birthday.
text_b: So he gave her cash.

text_a: Larry bought a new motorcycle. He was excited to look cool. The first time he tried riding it he dropped it. He hurt his leg and had to go to the hospital.
text_b: Larry loved going to the hospital.
